knowledge_graph.title: Crispbread
knowledge_graph.description: Crispbread is a flat and dry type of bread, containing mostly rye flour. Crispbreads are lightweight and keep fresh for a very long time due to their lack of water. Crispbread is a staple food and was for a long time considered a poor man's diet.

related_questions.question: Is crispbread better for you than bread?
related_questions.snippet: The high amount of fiber found in crispbread and, as many people mistakenly believe that it is low in calories, is the reason why people choose to eat crispbread on a diet. Meanwhile, what may surprise you, crispbread has no fewer calories than regular bread.
related_questions.title: Crispbread on a diet - eat it or not?

related_questions.question: What do Swedes eat with crispbread?
related_questions.snippet: Crispbread comes in various shapes, thicknesses and flavours, with entire store shelves devoted to it. People top it with anything from sliced boiled eggs with tube caviar (breakfast), to ham, cheese and cucumber slices (lunch), to just plain butter as a side dish (dinner).
related_questions.title: 10 things to know about Swedish food | sweden.se

related_questions.question: How do Norwegians eat crispbread?
related_questions.snippet: Full of healthy seeds and oats, these wonderful Norwegian crisp breads are delicious served simply with butter, but also work well with cheese, jam, dips, pâté and ham.

related_questions.question: Is Wasa crispbread healthy?
related_questions.snippet: Whole Grain is the #1 ingredient in this product Whole grains provide a good source of fiber, B vitamins and iron. They may also reduce the risk of heart disease and diabetes and are linked to lower body weight.

buttons.subtitle: Crispbread Ingredient
buttons.title: Crispbread - Wikipedia
buttons.snippet: Crispbread traditionally consists of wholemeal rye flour, salt, and water. Today, however, many kinds of crispbread contain wheat flour, spices and grains, and are often leavened with yeast or sourdough, and milk or sesame seeds can be added.
